TITLE: Generating Green Pixel Video for Shaka Player Testing (Bash)
DESCRIPTION: This bash script creates a 10-second video of a green pixel for testing purposes. It generates 300 frames of a 32x32 green pixel image, then uses ffmpeg to combine them into a 320x180 MP4 video at 30fps.
SOURCE: https://github.com/shaka-project/shaka-player/blob/main/test/test/assets/green-pixel.txt#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
mkdir -p pixel

# Create a 32x32 green pixel image
convert xc:#008000[32x32] pixel/pixel0.png

# Copy it to make 300 frames
for i in $(seq 1 299); do cp pixel/pixel0.png pixel/pixel$i.png; done

# Combine the frames into a 30fps, 10s video, scaled up to 320x180
ffmpeg -r 30 -i pixel/pixel%d.png \
  -c:v h264 -vf fps=30 -pix_fmt yuv420p -preset veryslow -tune stillimage \
  -vf scale=320:180 \
  -y test/test/assets/green-pixel.mp4
```

